                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d263">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Egan</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santiago</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1891-12-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 22, 1891</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Egan reports that the Argentine minister made representations on the previous
                    day to the minister for foreign affairs as dean of the diplomatic corps, who
                    promised that only the police officers in uniform would be left around the
                    legation and the detectives should be withdrawn. He states that the annoyances
                    have been abated, but not removed, and the promise made by the foreign office
                    complied with in part only.</p>
            </div>
